statement: You enjoy quietly providing loyal personal service to others, staying out of the spotlight yourself.
You prefer to support and encourage others rather than to lead.
You show an unusual ability to be loyal and forgiving toward persons who mistreat you.
You enjoy being unpredictable and doing things without planning ahead.
You believe that anything is possible, and don't like to rule out solutions that others say have no real possibility of success.
You have your own strong sense of taste, art, and/or style.
You do not mind doing the same kinds of work over and over again.
You have strong opinions about the way things should be, but usually do not express them unless asked.
You like following set routines in most aspects of your life and rarely do things that are out of your ordinary habits.
You really understand the way machines or processes work, and how to fix them when they don't.
You often see problems or errors in theories or untested plans and are able to explain them to others (you can tell them what will not work and why).
You sometimes choose to behave according to your own rules just because you "feel like it."
You often tell people how they should behave toward other people.
You sometimes have trouble deciding whether to make people take responsibility for their actions or to save them from their actions.
You easily express your emotions.
You like practically anything that is NEW.
You can usually make almost anything FUN.
Other people say you talk non-stop.
When giving advice or instructions to others, you usually tell them that it is very important that they be fully committed to whatever it is you are helping them with.
You like to do things the way that they have always been done because those ways have been proven to work.
You readily learn and actively enforce the rules and do not like to break the rules.
You enjoy saying and doing things to shock or surprise others.
You like to fool others by "playing dumb" (pretending to not understand things when you really do understand them).
You are comfortable giving and answering high-risk challenges.
You actively work to improve society to help people who are helpless or in crisis.
It's easy for you to figure out the motives and private problems of other people.
You really don't like public recognition for things you do, and may shift the praise to others.
You believe that most people are good, by nature.
You have an active imagination, often seeing human characteristics in toys or other objects.
You choose to believe in the good in the world and try to understand why people might do bad things.
You are skilled at developing new systems or making existing systems work better.
You have the confidence to start a project with little or no input from others.
You easily move away from the "way things have always been done" in pursuing tasks or personal interests.
You often do things with the purpose of making yourself smarter.
You naturally analyze things, trying to find out WHY things are as they are.
You are able to lose yourself in thought, often being unaware of objects and activities in your surroundings.
Many people regard you as their best friend  (You speak of even people you haven't known very long as being "good friends.")
You are comfortable being the person who holds a group together.
People often go to you for advice and support.
You do impressions of other people for fun - acting like other people to entertain friends.
You show warmth/emotions/affect but usually through your actions rather than words.
People might say that you "have never met a stranger" or that you are comfortable talking with people you have just met.
You have your own set of principles or values which you are able to defend with any number of convincing logical arguments.
You often have better ideas for doing things that others may have already planned, and might even enjoy talking others into doing it your way.
You don't mind telling other people they are wrong, especially when they disagree with you.
You enjoy creatively making up things with words/thoughts/ideas.
You enjoy creating "masterpieces" (inventions, concepts, techniques that previously did not exist).
You really are a unique person, one-of-a-kind.
